Epigyne (Fig. 12
D-F
): dark with a lighter mark in the center. Scape short, approximately two to three times wider than long. Posterior and lateral margin weakly sclerotized, slightly protruding beyond the epigynal posterior margin (Fig. 12D). Spermathecae nearly ovoid, separated by about 1.5 diameters (Fig. 12F). Fertilization ducts thin and long, reaching the spermathecae with 3.5 coils. Copulatory ducts short, slightly narrower at their distal end (Fig. 12
E-F
).
